<item>
            <title>[LU-15981] cascading_rw fails with enospc when osts are small</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15981</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On unlink ost object destroys get delayed until osp_sync_thread decides to cancel unlink records. This makes cascading_rw test to fail due to enospc if OSTs are not big enough as the test consumes disk space faster that osp_sync_thread generates OST_DESTROYs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;OSTSIZE=200000 SLOW=yes sh parallel-scale.sh should  be enough to see the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
